Smallest Missing Positive Number
Last Updated : 23 Jul, 2025
Given an unsorted array arr[] with both positive and negative elements, find the smallest positive number missing from the array.

Examples:

Input: arr[] = [2, -3, 4, 1, 1, 7]
Output: 3
Explanation: 3 is the smallest positive number missing from the array.

Input: arr[] = [5, 3, 2, 5, 1]
Output: 4
Explanation: 4 is the smallest positive number missing from the array.

Input: arr[] = [-8, 0, -1, -4, -3]
Output: 1 
Explanation: 1 is the smallest positive number missing from the array.

my first brute force 
class Solution {
  public:
    int missingNumber(vector<int> &arr) {
        // code here
        int n=arr.size();
        int missing=arr[0];
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                if(i!=arr[j]){
                    missing=i;// this will not give the min of the positive number and keep replacing the value
                }
                else break;//also a problem 
            }
        }
        return missing;
    }
};

2nd approach with chatgpt help
class Solution {
  public:
    int missingNumber(vector<int> &arr) {
        // code here
        int n=arr.size();
        for(int i=1;i<=n+1;i++){//for the edge case in case all the number are positive so the smallest missing positive number is the the n+1
            bool found=false;//using boolean flag
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                if(i==arr[j]){
                    found=true;
                }
            }
            if(found==false){//checking after traversing all the element because in the previous app i was changing the number immdiately not thinking
about if it came after
                return i;
            }
        }
        return n+1;
    }
};
complexity of space O(1)
time comp is O(n^2)
